<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n01033j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01033j">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01033j"> 33(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ sale in articles, match / pattern line, ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[GRADING THE SHOPPER. By A FIRST SALESWOMAN.]</font>There is the &ldquo;pattern line&rdquo; &mdash;the woman who seems to devote her life to collecting patterns and appears never to make a purchase. The <mark>&ldquo;match pattern line&rdquo;</mark> is the woman who demonstrates what size pattern she wants so carefully that it is obvious she wants a free patch for a worn-out suit or costume of that material. <small> <a name="DM17nov22" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#DM17nov22"><cite title="source">Daily Mail</cite></a> (17 November 1922) 8/5</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05111h" href="c05all.htm#c05111h">VI.C.05:111(h)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
